## Project Summary

Fractal is an AI-powered idea synthesis tool that maps relationships between concepts and presents them as an expandable visual network. It is not a search engine — it shows structural forces, tensions, and emergent patterns shaping a big question.

**Current Status:** Demo built with hardcoded data for one query. Basic node/edge visual rendering works. Next step is connecting a live LLM backend.

-----

## Architecture Decision: Two Paths

### The Core Decision

- **Ollama** = local development environment (free, offline, your machine)
- **Groq** = deployed demo/mockup (free tier API, internet accessible, real users)

Same underlying model (Llama 3) runs in both places, keeping behavior consistent.

-----

## Path 1 — Development Architecture (Ollama)

```
Developer Machine
│
├── Frontend (React / your UI framework)
│     └── sends query to local backend
│
├── Backend (FastAPI or Node server)
│     └── receives query
│     └── formats structured JSON prompt
│     └── sends to Ollama on localhost
│
└── Ollama (running locally on port 11434)
      └── runs Llama 3 model on your machine
      └── returns structured JSON map
      └── backend validates + transforms
      └── frontend renders graph
```

**Key points:**

- Nothing leaves your machine
- No API keys needed
- No rate limits
- No cost ever
- Use this to build, test, and iterate on prompts
- Break things freely here — no consequences

-----

## Path 2 — Production/Demo Architecture (Groq)

```
User (anywhere in the world)
│
└── Browser
      └── sends query to your deployed frontend
            │
            └── Deployed Backend (e.g. Railway, Render, or Vercel)
                  └── receives query
                  └── formats structured JSON prompt
                  └── sends to Groq API (over internet)
                        │
                        └── Groq servers run Llama 3
                        └── returns structured JSON map
                  └── backend validates + transforms
                  └── frontend renders graph
                  └── user sees their Fractal map
```

**Key points:**

- Groq free tier handles solid demo traffic
- Fast — Groq is actually faster than OpenAI
- Swap from Ollama to Groq = change API URL + API key + model name (~10 min)
- When free tier runs out, paid Groq is much cheaper than OpenAI/Anthropic
- This is what investors, users, and your team interact with

-----

## Switching Between Paths

The only things that change between Ollama (dev) and Groq (prod):

|              |Ollama (Dev)          |Groq (Prod)              |
|--------------|----------------------|-------------------------|
|API URL       |http://localhost:11434|https://api.groq.com     |
|API Key       |none needed           |GROQ_API_KEY             |
|Model name    |llama3                |llama3-8b-8192           |
|Who can access|only you              |everyone                 |
|Cost          |free                  |free tier → then low cost|

Everything else — the prompt, the JSON schema, the validation logic, the frontend — stays identical.

